<h1>A Blog About Pizza</h1>
<p>Pizza is a mouth watering Italian Fastfood which made in the late 1600's. Raffaele Esposito, an Italian chef and owner of a tavern in Naples, is considered by some to be the father of modern pizza1. He is credited with inventing the margherita pizza in the late 1800s2. Although street vendors in Naples sold flatbreads with toppings before then, Esposito's contribution is significant in the history of pizza3. The first documented use of the name "pizza" appeared in the city of Gaeta in 997 C.E. </p>
<h2>Ingredients of Pizza</h2>
The basic ingredients of pizza are:
Flour, Tomato Sauce, Pizza Dough, Yeast, Chesse and Vegetables.